{ UID: uid-3592-f387-6662-8d44
  is: article
  title: "Welcome to Cyrus for Minecraft Programming"
  text: "Cyrus lets you program Minecraft with 'spells'."
        "On the right you'll see your first Minecraft spell."
        "It should look something like this:"
        "|["
        "{ is: editable minecraft spell"
        "  title: \"First Cyrus Spell\""
        "  Rules: {"
        "  }"
        "  world: http://localhost:8084/o/uid-b1d8-d170-a3d9-e693.json"
        "  player: http://localhost:8084/o/uid-06b6-4631-166a-b013.json"
        "}"
        "]|"
        "If you hit the link after 'world:', you'll be able to see the state of the world - time of day, raining or snowing."
        "If you hit the link after 'player:', you'll be able to see your player coordinates in the world. Watch it change as you move around. Copy the three coordinates - you're going to need them in the next step."
}

{ UID: uid-4ee8-9084-8ab0-6a2b
  is: article
  title: "Placing some blocks"
  text: "Now edit the spell - by selecting the text apart from the links:"
        "|["
        "{ is: editable minecraft spell"
        "  title: \"First Cyrus Spell\""
        "  Rules: {"
      "![    is: spell rule]!"
      "![    placing: => glass box ( 1 1 1 ) at ( x y z )]!"
      "![    Notifying: => @. with @world]!"
        " }"
        "  world: http://localhost:8084/o/uid-b1d8-d170-a3d9-e693.json"
        "  player: http://localhost:8084/o/uid-06b6-4631-166a-b013.json"
        "}"
        "]|"
        "/[Note: you must set the coordinates 'x y z' to your own player coordinates, copied from the player: object.]/"
        "Press the 'Update' button below this text to make the change. If it doesn't seem to work, hit refresh."
        "This will place a glass box of size 1x1x1 at the coordinates given."
        "The Notifying line is to tell the world about this spell."
        "Try other box sizes (like '5 4 7' - not too big!) and material names like 'sand-stone', 'stone', 'ore-gold', etc"
        "Note: Edit the rule, not the spell!"
}

{ UID: uid-1a57-fa37-17a0-8672
  is: article
  title: "Glass trails"
  text: "This is a spell to leave a trail of glass everywhere you go."
        "It's a bit clumsy, finding and setting the player coordinates ourselves. Let's get the spell to do it for us:"
        "|["
        "  Rules: {"
        "    is: spell rule"
      "![    placing: => glass box ( 1 1 1 ) at ( @player:position + ( 3 0 3 ))]!"
        "    Notifying: => @. with @world"
        "  }"
        "]|"
        "We take the player position, push it out three blocks."
}

{ UID: uid-6672-f066-5321-d37f
  is: article
  title: "Scanning the blocks in the world"
  text: "Now add a scanner to the spell, which tells the world we'd like to be updated on the blocks in some region. The region will be -50 down from where we stand:"
        "|["
        " Rules: {"
        "   is: spell rule"
        "   placing: => glass box ( 1 1 1 ) at ( @player:position + ( 3 0 3 ))"
      "![   scanning: =>      box ( 2 3 4 ) at ( @player:position + ( 0 -50 0 ))]!"
        "   Notifying: => @. with @world"
        " }"
        "]|"
        "If you jump the link after 'world', then the link at 'block-lists', you'll see your results: as you move around, you see different blocks. Try to find some air underground, indicating a cave."
        "This is a bit inconvenient, and not easy to get to from our spell, Luckily we're told about it in our spell. The other end of 'Notifying' is 'Alerted':"
        "|["
      "![ {]!"
      "![   is: spell rule]!"
      "![   Alerted: { is: minecraft block list }]!"
      "![   scan-blocks: # => @Alerted]!"
      "![ } ]!"
        "]|"
        "Now you'll see a link 'scan-blocks:' right in our spell. Much more convenient."
}

